'''Brzeg water tower''' - a historic [[water tower]] in the town of [[Brzeg]], [[Opole Voivodeship]], [[Poland]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Staśkiewicz|first1=Jarosław|title=Wieża ciśnień w Brzegu w rękach harcerzy|url=http://www.nto.pl/wiadomosci/brzeg/art/4538131,wieza-cisnien-w-brzegu-w-rekach-harcerzy,id,t.html|website=nto.pl|accessdate=24 August 2017|language=pl}}</ref>
When the oldest waterworks for the town of [[Brzeg]] (''Brieg''), built in the second half of the nineteenth-century was not sufficient for the town's populous, in 1864, the town authorities set out to built a new water tower which was completed in the latter part of the aforesaid year. Initially, water was taken from the [[Oder]] River, however, due to noted frequent epidemics, a waterworks was built in [[Gierszowice]] to supply the [[water tower]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Wieża ciśnień, Brzeg - Zabytek.pl|url=https://zabytek.pl/pl/obiekty/wieza-cisnien-3106|website=zabytek.pl|accessdate=24 August 2017|language=pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Brzeg - Wieża ciśnień - stare zdjęcia, mapa|url=http://fotopolska.eu/Brzeg/b16723,Wieza_cisnien.html|website=fotopolska.eu|accessdate=24 August 2017}}</ref>
