'''Victor Mravlag''', MD was [[Mayor of Elizabeth, New Jersey]] who served multiple terms, he was also a physician who was instrumental in the development of the [http://www.elizabethtownhf.org/elizabeth_general_historical_material.htm Elizabeth General Hospital and Dispensary].  Dr. Mravlag was a member of the [http://www.unioncountymedicalsociety.org Union County Medical Society] and a founding member of the Elizabeth General Hospital Clinical Society.

==Biography==
He died on May 15, 1934.<ref>{{cite news |author= |title=Noted Mayor Dies. Chief Executive of Elizabeth, N.J., Aided Needy and Attended 4,000 Births. Backed Sunday Movies, Threatened to Close Streets to Autos and Trolley Cars if Pictures Were Banned  |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1934/05/16/archives/noted-ayor-dies-chief-executive-of-elizabeth-n-j-aided-needy-and.html |quote= |newspaper=[[New York Times]] |date=May 16, 1934 }}</ref>

